  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Manufacturing Enginner / Manager",
  "description": "<h2>Job Title</h2><p><strong>Manufacturing / Production Engineer (Automotive Vehicle Components Fabrication & Repair  )</strong></p><p><em></em></p><h2>Responsibilities</h2><h3><strong>Manufacturing & Production (Primary Scope)</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Plan, organise and supervise <strong>manufacturing and fabrication operations</strong> for vehicle-related metal components, including brackets, guards, supports and structural accessories.</p></li><li><p>Develop, improve and control <strong>manufacturing processes</strong>, work methods and production workflow to enhance productivity, quality and cost efficiency.</p></li><li><p>Oversee fabrication activities such as <strong>cutting, drilling, bending, welding, grinding and spray painting</strong>, ensuring compliance with quality and safety standards.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate closely with <strong>suppliers and subcontractors</strong> on materials, components, tooling and delivery schedules.</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>production quality inspections</strong>, implement corrective and preventive actions, and maintain technical documentation and SOPs.</p></li><li><p>Supervise and guide <strong>junior technicians and production staff</strong>, allocate work and monitor workmanship consistency.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Automotive Engineering & Repair (Integrated Scope)</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Lead <strong>vehicle inspection, diagnostics and troubleshooting</strong>, including mechanical failure investigation and root-cause analysis.</p></li><li><p>Plan and oversee <strong>repair, servicing and overhaul activities</strong> for automotive systems, ensuring technical accuracy and reliability.</p></li><li><p>Translate <strong>customer and operational feedback</strong> into manufacturing or repair process improvements.</p></li><li><p>Provide <strong>technical advice</strong> to customers, dealers and internal teams on vehicle condition, repair feasibility and improvement options.</p></li><li><p>Support evaluation activities related to <strong>buying and selling of vehicles</strong>, including technical condition assessment.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Continuous Improvement & Coordination</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Identify opportunities for <strong>process optimisation</strong> across manufacturing and repair operations.</p></li><li><p>Participate in <strong>customer or dealer discussions / focus sessions</strong> when required to support product or service enhancement.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety, operational and regulatory requirements.</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Bachelor’s Degree</strong> in Mechanical Engineering / Manufacturing Engineering or equivalent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Minimum 10 years</strong> of relevant experience in <strong>automotive mechanical engineering</strong>, manufacturing or production environment.</p></li><li><p>Strong <strong>hands-on practical experience</strong> in vehicle repair, diagnostics and mechanical systems.</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in <strong>metal fabrication / manufacturing processes</strong> is highly preferred.</p></li><li><p>Experience related to <strong>vehicle trading (buying and selling)</strong> is an added advantage.</p></li><li><p>Able to supervise staff, work with suppliers, and communicate effectively with customers.</p></li></ul>",
